<Author>Drifting_clouds
<Content>Don't believe Lonely Planet guidebook!!!!! We made an unexpected stay in San Juan with short notice. As we were traveling I had no real access to a computer so trusted in my guidebook Puerto Rico which is published by Lonely Planet and which I just bought at the airport bookstore. They gave this hotel a very good review. I have never felt more betrayed by the guidebook in my life! It was awful, one of the worst places we have ever stayed in worldwide in 40+ years of traveling. The place looked like maybe 10-15 years ago it MIGHT have been nice but it has been neglected for a long, long time. It was sooooooooo depressing and grim. Not the sort of thing you want on a vacation, to be somewhere that you can't stand to spend one waking moment in the room. I would not say it was very dirty but it is extremely shabby. Torn curtains that are half hanging off rod and can't open or close (those were dirty as was bedspread but floor and bathroom was pretty clean if you overlook someone else's hairs on walls in shower etc). Torn and battered lamp. Room phones don't work. Very noisy old air conditioning unit. No water for shower or sink or to flush toilet for most of one day. Upstairs terrace has no water in the fountain and weeds in the planters, looked like no one had been up there for a long time. People that worked there seemed nice and friendly but the place itself is so darn unpleasant I would never recommend it to anyone!Also the neighborhood didn't feel very safe with bars on all the windows and broken sidewalks. 
