<Author>TAINE
<Content>Don't Even think About It ! I had to overnight in San Juan on Jan 20 and didn't know that on Jan 19-22 San Juan celebrates a big fiesta named la feria de la calle de San Sebastian. All the hotels were solid booked and the hotel Mgr who helped me found one room left at this Iberia Hotel.The outside looks pretty attractive with his spanish casa style and its little garden. The only room left was a 2 queen bedroom and the Manager (from Spain)priced it $132 because it was supposed to fit 4 people...Since my only other option to sleep in San Juan that night was the airport lounge...I paid and could see that the credit card receipt was untitled  garden supplies  ! So first thought = there is something strange about this hotel !!Room 307 has indeed 2 queen beds but of a terrible quality and then I found that there was no phone next to the phone directory !! + no shower head in the shower meaning that you cannot use it (great way to save water !) + no soap, no shampoo, no tooth cups, no washclothes...I could find one maid who brought 2 tiny soap bars and 2 plastic cups but that was it..The most unbeleivable is that there are metallic shades and a piece of vinyl as a window meaning that you are like sleeping outside and you get all the noise from the street, the parking lot and the building near the hotel. Of course I could not sleep more than a few hours and when I made my comments to the Mgr the next morning, he said that there were 150 guests in the hotel and that I was the only one to be complaining ...that to get a shower, we just need water and soap (his words !) + the phone line was down but no big deal etc...etc...I requested a partial refund but he said that even if I would have left the hotel the night before, he would have charged me because cancellation must be made 48hrs in advance !!!! Well, I don't think that I need to add anything to make the readers understand that you should NEVER pick up this hotel in San Juan even in the worse situations ! I would have accepted some conditions if I would have paid $50 but for $132 I felt totally exploited. So my recommendation is to stay away from this hotel and hopefully the Manager could know about all those bad feedbacks found in Tripadvisor. ODILE 
