<Content>Stay Away Where do I start. Booked 3 nights but stayed only 2 b/c I could only cancel  get a full refund for 1 night- and for that I had to endure the arrogance  mysoginism of the front desk Mgr. The lame un-helpful clerk for the 2 nights completed the experience. Early that night the elec. went out-there were no flashlights to pass around the only response from the clerk was a blank,don't care stare. This is a subpar place that misrepresents itself as a hotel. Their exterior small reception area is charming very Old World Spanish-this MUST be their bait. The Mgr pointed out that their customers are mostly traveling students-ie, the strapped for cash w/ no hostels nearby crowd. Room was dark w/very worn furniture,had an acrid smell that would not go away even though I left the pane windows open w/the a/c running, vynil shower curtains were coated w/soap scum,  a tiny awkward bathroom u had to step up to to get into (per Mgr all bathrooms were like this). It had an armoire instead of a closet  b/c of the lack of space TV was propped on a ceiling corner. I asked to see a larger room-it was worse- w/ the bedspreads threadbare.There is no elevator. It was $79 per night  this was NOT a good value as there ARE much better places for that price range-for example, the EL PRADO INN- so please check around. Anything good?: the maid kept the room dustfree. 
